he approach and safely land/stop."},{h:"Takeoff Decision Point (TDP)",p:"The point on the takeoff path at which the pilot decides whether to reject (before TDP) or continue (after TDP) the takeoff following an engine failure."},{h:"Landing Decision Point (LDP)",p:"The last point on the landing profile at which the height/airspeed combination permits the decision to continue the landing or to accelerate to VTOSS and climb away."},{h:"Takeoff Safety Speed (VTOSS)",p:"The airspeed assuring a steady climb of at least 100 fpm with 2.5-min power (OEI) at the max gross mass for the ambient condition. VTOSS = 50 KIAS."},{h:"Best Rate-of-climb Speed (VY)",p:"The airspeed giving the greatest gain in altitude in a given time. VY = 65 KIAS."}]},{id:"wl-xmsn-oil-press",cat:"emergencies",group:"Warning Lights",title:"XMSN OIL PRESS",kind:"procedure",ref:{src:"FM",loc:"§3.2.1 · p. 3-8",rev:"5A"},lamps:[{caption:"XMSN OIL PRESS",type:"warning"}],indications:["Transmission oil pressure below minimum","– Transmission oil pressure indication 1 bar or less"],blocks:[{k:"note",t:"XMSN OIL PRESS warning light may come on momentarily during extreme side slip, sidewards flight, crosswind hover or slope operations."},{k:"sub",t:"If one XMSN oil pressure indication is below minimum:"},{k:"step",a:"Power",i:"Reduce"},{k:"land",level:"practicable"},{k:"sub",t:"If both indications are below 1 bar:"},{k:"land",level:"immediately"},{k:"note",t:"Descend with minimum power."}]},{id:"wl-rotor-rpm",cat:"emergencies",group:"Warning Lights",title:"ROTOR RPM",kind:"procedure",ref:{src:"FM",loc:"§3.2.1 · p. 3-7",rev:"5A"},lamps:[{caption:"ROTOR RPM",type:"warning"}],indications:["NRo low — NRo 95% or less — Audio signal: steady tone","NRo high — NRo 106% or more — Audio signal: none"],blocks:[{k:"step",a:"Collective lever",i:"Adjust as necessary to maintain NRo within normal operating range"}]},{id:"wl-bat-disch",cat:"emergencies",group:"Warning Lights",title:"BAT DISCH",kind:"procedure",ref:{src:"FM",lo