 mass of the helicopter.","Lowering or raising the collective lever will result in a left or right yawing motion to a degree dependent upon the tail rotor thrust remaining.","Approach and landing should be made with a suitable rate of descent, controlling sideslip angle with the collective lever. If the situation permits, a crosswind landing should be performed to minimize sideslip. Before touchdown, reduce groundspeed to a minimum and touch down with the skids aligned with the direction of landing.",{h:"Right pedal fixed-pitch setting",p:"Raising the collective lever results in a right yawing motion. Lower the collective lever to control sideslip and touch down with forward speed."},{h:"Left pedal fixed-pitch setting",p:"Lowering the collective lever results in a left yawing motion. Approach with a right sideslip and reduce ground speed to allow raising the collective lever as necessary to touchdown."}]},{id:"elec-bat-bus",cat:"emergencies",group:"Electrical / System",title:"Electrical Short Circuit — Battery Bus / Feeder Line",ref:{src:"FM",loc:"§3.6.2 · p. 3-62",rev:"5A"},kind:"procedure",lamps:[{caption:"BAT DISCH",type:"warning"}],indications:["– Short circuit on battery bus or battery feeder line","– Power supply interrupted to battery only","– Power supply guaranteed to all consumer busses by the generators","– BAT DISCH warning light on (prolonged or for short period)","– Both BUS-TIE switches OFF"],blocks:[{k:"sub",t:"If BAT DISCH warning light remains on:"},{k:"step",a:"PWR SELECT switch",i:"OFF"},{k:"step",a:"Ammeter and voltmeter",i:"Monitor"},{k:"land",level:"practicable"},{k:"note",t:"Emergency battery power will not be available."}]},{id:"fuel-valve",cat:"emergencies",group:"Electrical / System",title:"FUEL VALVE I / II",ref:{src:"FM",loc:"§3.2 · p. 3-25",rev:"5A"},kind:"procedure",lamps:[{caption:"FUEL VALVE I",type:"caution"},{caption:"FUEL VALVE II",type:"caution"}],indications:["Fuel valve is in a position other than commanded"],blocks:[{k:"note",